article_title: One Injured In Crash Involving Semi, Car Near Frontier City - News9.com - Oklahoma City, OK - News, Weather, Video and Sports
article_text:
One person was injured in a crash involving a semi-truck and a car on Interstate 35 near Frontier City in Oklahoma City, Friday morning.

Bob Mills SkyNews 9 HD flew over the scene. Pilot Jim Gardner reported that two lanes of I-35 northbound were shut down just south of the Britton exit. One person inside the car suffered minor injuries.

Traffic was backed up in northbound I-35 in the area.
